[Plague is caused by _Yersinia (formerly _Pasteurella_) pestis_ and affects
primarily the lymphatics and lungs. Plague is a historic scourge of man,
wild rodents, and rabbits and cases associated with cats, dogs and camels
are now recognized as hazards to man.
The primary means of spreading _Yersinia pestis_ is the flea. Contact with
infected carcasses has been a significant source of infection for man.
Endemic foci of sylvatic plague exists in the western USA and in many areas
worldwide. Throughout history, outbreaks of human plague involving rats in
densely populated agricultural or urban areas have occurred when rats
commingled with infected sylvatic rodents. - Mod.TG
